properties.narrative: Four narrow waterspouts were observed to the southwest of Fort Zachery Taylor State Park in Key West. Due to distance, no spray rings were visible.
An airplane pilot reported a waterspout associated with a thunderstorm over the local Atlantic waters off the coast of Miami-Dade County.
Waterspout observed offshore of Windy Hill Beach.
A waterspout was spotted near Isla de Cabras in Toa Baja.
Waterspout spotted 8 miles west southwest of Honeydew, CA.
Two waterspouts were observed about 2 miles south of the Channel 5 Bridge. One waterspout had a visible spray ring. The waterspouts moved toward the east about 10 to 15 knots.
A strong low over the eastern Pacific Ocean sent an associated trough to the southern Oregon coast. Waterspouts developed as this trough neared the coast.
A strong low over the eastern Pacific Ocean sent an associated trough to the southern Oregon coast. Waterspouts developed as this trough neared the coast.
A waterspout was observed south of the Boca Chica Bridge. No spray ring was observed and the condensation funnel extended halfway down from cloud base.
Several weak waterspouts were observed south of Boca Chica Key. Each waterspout was narrow and very short-lived. No spray rings were observed.

Two waterspouts were observed southwest of Bahia Honda Key. One waterspout extended one quarter to one third of the way down from cloud base, was very narrow, and had no spray ring. The second waterspout was also narrow, only extended one fifth the way down from cloud base, with no spray ring observed.
Public reported a waterspout approaching shore just south of Ben T Davis Beach near the Courtney Campbell Causeway. No reports of it moving ashore were received, with no associated damage reported.
Emergency managers received reports of a waterspout just off the coast of Arecibo, near Marginal PR-2.
Media shared social media image of a waterspout south of Biloxi Beach. Time is radar estimated.
Broadcast media relayed report of a waterspout in Charlotte Harbor offshore Pine Island just north of Bokeelia.
A picture from social media showed a waterspout funnel east of Hollywood Beach over the local Atlantic waters as a thunderstorm moved through the area.
A waterspout was observed northwest of Key West via the NWS and several mariners. The waterspout was relatively wide, had a confirmed spray ring, with its duration approximately 30 minutes.
Waterspout was reported in the Currituck Sound.
Broadcast media relayed report of a waterspout offshore Anna Maria Island just north of Bean Point.
A waterspout was visible from the National Weather Service office in Lake Charles. The waterspout was over the north end of Calcasieu Lake.
Received photo of waterspout offshore Port Clinton. Location of waterspout estimated.
Report and photos of a waterspout offshore Yscloskey in Lake Borgne.

At least three waterspouts were observed just northwest of Howe Key by the Monroe County Deputy Emergency Manager and several members of the public. One notable, vertical, mature condensation funnel with an attendant spray ring was observed, while at least two other narrow, rope-link mature waterspouts were observed simultaneously.
A waterspout was sighted on the Galveston Bay side of the Bolivar Peninsula.
Picture of a thin waterspout over Bay St Louis relayed by broadcast media. Time and location estimated by radar.
Photos and videos of a waterspout on Lake Pontchartrain relayed by the public on social media. Time and location estimated by radar.
A waterspout was reported over Florida Bay west northwest of Channel Five Bridge. The report was relayed by the Monroe County Sheriffs Office.
A waterspout was observed south of Cudjoe Bay. The report was relayed as a photo via social media.
A waterspout was reported via social media. The waterspout consisted of a narrow condensation funnel observed about halfway down to the horizon from the cloud base.
A waterspout was observed in marsh approximately 5 miles east of Golden Meadow.
Video showed a waterspout develop just offshore of the Canton neighborhood, then moving onshore.
There were photos and video footage of a waterspout near Tyndall AFB on social media.
Public reported a short-lived waterspout southwest of Blind Pass offshore Sanibel Island.
A pilot reported a waterspout associated with a shower east of Miami Beach.
Broadcast media relayed video of a waterspout observed approximately 8 miles offshore of Venice.
A video on social media showed a waterspout approximately 10 miles southwest of Leeville. The location and time were estimated from radar.
A waterspout was sighted just off the coast of Jamaica Beach.
A waterspout was sighted just off the coast of Surfside Beach.
The public reported a waterspout offshore from Panama City Beach via phone call and photos on social media.

Webcam video and a separate public cell phone video of a brief waterspout near Tofte on Lake Superior was received. The location and the duration were estimated, but no damage was reported as it remained offshore.
A waterspout occurred off the coast of Jamaica Beach.

Waterspout reported over Saginaw Bay approximately 2 miles off shore, roughly 5 miles west of Port Austin. It continued tracking NE staying just offshore passing just north of Port Austin Harbor. Last report stated it was just north of Grindstone City just before 7pm EDT.
Waterspout photographed offshore Vermilion around 6:45 AM EDT. Location approximated based on Doppler radar data.
A waterspout was spotted just offshore of Cape San Blas.
A waterspout was observed and reported via social media north northeast of Marathon. A spray ring was observed.
Dare County 911 Center relayed public reports of waterspouts on the leading flank of thunderstorms moving through the Croatan and Pamlico Sounds.

Multiple photos of a waterspout and funnel were reported via social media. The waterspout occurred either in the intracoastal waters or Atlantic waters near Fernandina Beach based on multiple vantage points. Looking east from Woodbridge Pkwy in Yulee, TJ Courson Rd looking south and looking southeast from the Osprey in St. Marys. Public also said a bridge may have been closed due to the waterspout. Time was estimated by radar.
A weather observer at ASOS station KPBI at West Palm Beach International Airport reported a waterspout associated with a shower just off the coast of West Palm Beach.
Social Media photo of a waterspout west of the Lake Pontchartrain Causeway. Time and location approximated from radar.
Social media video of two waterspouts over Lake Pontchartrain seen from the I-10 Twin Span bridge. Time and location estimated from radar.
Two short-lived waterspouts were spotted off Oak Island.
A lifeguard reported a waterspout off of South Forest Beach on Hilton Head Island.
Multiple pictures of twin waterspouts in the southern part of Lake Pontchartrain.
Picture of waterspout just north of Lakefront Airport.
Additional pictures of a waterspout ongoing just north of Kenner.
Members of the public reported a waterspout off the coast of Marco Island associated with a shower moving through the area.
Waterspout confirmed off Cherry Grove Beach.
Local broadcast media relayed a report from the public of a waterspout just off the coast of Isle of Palms. Multiple images of the waterspout were also posted on social media.
Waterspout was observed by the emergency manager.

A narrow, tilted waterspout was observed via the WFO Key West roof camera approximately 16 miles north northwest of Big Coppitt Key. The condensation funnel cloud extended about one fifth the way from the cloud base to the horizon. The waterspout moved toward the west-northwest around 10 knots.
Photo of a waterspout was captured and shared on social media.
A waterspout was photographed offshore over Lake Michigan from south of Cross Village near the end of Island View Rd.
Early morning thunderstorms produced multiple reports of waterspouts offshore of Panama City on July 17th.
Facebook post from Public with pic of waterspout taken from Pass Christian, MS.
Video of waterspout near Lake Catherine relayed via social media.
NCDOT Ferry Division boat captain reported a waterspout near the mouth of the Pamlico River.
A mariner participating in a fishing tournament reported a waterspout that lasted just over 10 minutes about 30 miles offshore.
Broadcast meteorologist relayed a picture of a waterspout on social media taken from Kingsmill in Williamsburg.
Broadcast media relayed a video of a waterspout over the Chesapeake Bay. The video was recorded from the public in Seaford.
Photo of small waterspout relayed via broadcast media. Time/location estimated from radar.
A trained spotter reported a waterspout east of Key Biscayne associated with a thunderstorm moving through the area.
Public relayed report via phone call of ongoing waterspout offshore west of Venice.
Video relayed through social media showed a waterspout near the Charleston jetties.
A Hilton Head Island city official reported a waterspout 10 miles offshore near the north end of the island.
Scattered thunderstorms produced wind gusts in excess of 34 knots along the coast and a waterspout just offshore of Panama City Beach during the July 21-24 time period.
Numerous reports via social media with photos and videos of a waterspout.
Waterspout photographed offshore Cedar Point Amusement Park. Location of waterspout approximated via radar data.
Broadcast media relayed report of a waterspout over Mobile Bay with photo from social media.
Early morning thunderstorms produced a waterspout off the west end of Panama City Beach on July 30th.
An off duty NWS employee reported via social media of a waterspout off the coast of Marco Island associated with a shower moving through the area.
Broadcast media shared pictures of a waterspout offshore Sanibel near Turner Beach.
Public pictures received from a local resident depicted a waterspout offshore Port Richey.
An airplane pilot reported a waterspout about 3 miles offshore, near Lake Worth, associated with a small thunderstorm.
Public shared a screen capture of a webcam video showing a waterspout offshore Treasure Island.
Waterspout observed over Inner Saginaw, northeast of Essexville. The waterspout lasted at least 5 minutes and tracked southeast before dissipating.

A mature waterspout was observed bayside of Marathon, moving eastward around 10 knots. The thin, tilted condensation funnel cloud extended all the way from the cloud base to the surface with a robust spray ring.
An off-duty National Weather Service meteorologist reported sighting a waterspout approximately four miles east-northeast of Deerfield Beach.

Two waterspouts were observed on the Atlantic side of Key Colony Beach and Coco Plum Beach, moving eastward around 10 knots. The thin, tilted condensation funnel clouds extended one-quarter of the way from cloud base to the horizon.
Public took photos and video of a waterspout over Lake Michigan near Leland.
Public reported to broadcast media a waterspout off of Englewood Beach. Location estimated by radar.
Received video of waterspout just offshore Mentor Headlands Beach Sate Park in Mentor Headlands area.
Waterspout offshore Mentor-on-the-Lake.
Received a report of a large waterspout over the Pamlico Sound near Cedar Island from a local media outlet WCTI.
Report of a waterspout was passed along via a resident of Bridgeton. Report stated the waterspout lasted no more than a minute.
The Patriot's Point Fire Division reported a waterspout in Charleston Harbor near Castle Pinckney.
A waterspout was observed north of Sugarloaf Key. The condensation funnel cloud had moderate width and was tilted.
Local broadcast media reported a waterspout over the Atlantic Ocean off the coast near Fort Lauderdale.

A narrow, tilted waterspout was observed at the range tower near the Northwest Channel. The condensation funnel cloud extended about one third of the way from the cloud base to the surface and no spray ring was observed. The waterspout moved slowly toward the west-southwest.
A member of the public reported a waterspout in the coastal waters of Punta Santiago, Humacao, and it was also seen from Naguabo.
Waterspout offshore Euclid.
The Fort Lauderdale Executive Airport ASOS site reported sighting a waterspout off the coast near Lauderdale-By-The-Sea.
A narrow, tilted waterspout was observed just east of No Name Key. The condensation funnel cloud extended almost completely to the surface, but no spray ring was observed.
Public reported a waterspout offshore Holiday lasting approximately 5 minutes from 8:07 until 8:12 PM EST.
Broadcast media shared images of waterspout over Charlotte Harbor.
The Emergency management team relayed a photo of a waterspout near Matanzas Inlet during the early evening hours of August 21st.
Multiple reports of twin waterspouts east of Manatee Lagoon and associated with a large thunderstorm complex over the Atlantic waters.

A cluster of strong thunderstorms and an outflow boundary moved from east to west across the area with measured wind gusts in excess of 34 knots and one report of a waterspout offshore of St George Island.
A video of a waterspout was shared. The waterspout was offshore of Atlantic Beach near Hanna Park.
A fair-weather waterspout with a spray ring was spotted from Humacao along a streamer of clouds downwind from Vieques.
The public posted a picture of a waterspout just off South Padre Island looking east from the causeway. Timing was based off their observation along with radar.

A waterspout observation was relayed by social media. The waterspout was observed approximately 4 miles west-northwest of Boca Chica Key and had a well-developed collar cloud and stout cone-shaped condensation funnel.
A waterspout was reported, via social media, to be seen over the Atlantic Ocean to the east of Deerfield Beach.
A waterspout was observed off the coast near Surfside Beach.
Various social media reports of a waterspout just offshore of Port Aransas.
A waterspout was sighted just to the east of Matagorda Beach.
Broadcast media relayed a public report, via social media, of a waterspout approximately three miles offshore Naples, seen that afternoon.
Broadcast media relayed reports of a waterspout off of Anna Maria Island.
Received a report from the public of a observed waterspout just offshore Cedar Island Ferry Terminal in the Pamlico Sound.
Multiple reports and pictures from the public of a waterspout offshore of the Cedar Island Ferry Terminal.
Report came in near the Haulover Day Use area in the Pamlico Sound. Report came in via a video and several pictures of the waterspout.
Several pictures and videos via social media of three separate waterspouts reported to the office. Locations were in the Pamlico Sound north of Frisco.
A report from social media showed a waterspout off the coast of Miami Beach associated with a shower in the area. Time is estimated from radar.
Broadcast media relayed public report of waterspout offshore of Turner Beach.
A member of the public reported a waterspout off the coast of Palm Beach County associated with a thunderstorm moving through the area.
Report received of a waterspout east of Patrick Space Force Base via the Space Force.
A waterspout was reported offshore of St George Island with pictures posted on social media.
A photo showed a waterspout several miles offshore, northeast of Burns Harbor.
A waterspout was reported several miles north of Burns Harbor.
A brief waterspout over Lake Erie occurred near Dunkirk.
A member of the public reported seeing a waterspout over the Atlantic Ocean off of Stuart Beach. It remained over the water.
The public reported a waterspout about 2 miles east or southeast of Miramar Beach.
Video report of a waterspout in Choctawhatchee Bay, just northeast of Santa Rosa Beach.
A spotter on social media posted a photo showing multiple waterspouts off the coast of Panama City.

A mature waterspout was observed south of Key West. The condensation cloud extended almost completely to the water surface. A spray ring was also visible. The waterspout moved slowly toward the north. The waterspout became obscured by rain after about 10 minutes.
A member of the broadcast media relayed a report of a waterspout off the coast of Naples associated with a shower moving through the area.

Report and photos of a waterspout via broadcast media located in the Pascagoula drainage basin. Photos and radar estimated position just north of Interstate 10 and west of Escatawpa/Highway 613. Time estimated from radar.

A narrow, rope-like waterspout was observed about 2 miles north of Bahia Honda Key. The condensation cloud extended all the way to the water surface. Video obtained later from a public observer verified a robust spray ring was attendant to the waterspout.
Public video via social media of a waterspout over/near Lake Catherine. Position estimated from radar and video.
Broadcast media relayed public report of waterspout offshore Manasota Key, corroborated by video of the waterspout captured by a webcam near Englewood.
Broadcast media shared a photo of a waterspout over Old Tampa Bay.
A social media post showed a waterspout over the northern end of Lake Okeechobee as a strong thunderstorm moved through the area.
Photos received via Facebook of large waterspout south of Marsh Island.
Broadcast media relayed a report of a waterspout near Captiva.

St. Johns County Emergency Management relayed a photo of a waterspout that approached the shore near Vilano Beach, FL. This waterspout was also reported by personnel at the Northeast Florida Regional Airport in St. Augustine, FL.

A nearly-vertical, elephant trunk-like, mature waterspout was reported via social media south of the Toms Harbor Cut Bridge. The condensation cloud extended all the way from the cloud base to the surface and a spray ring was present. The movement was northwestward around 10 to 15 knots.

A waterspout was sighted over Little Traverse Bay with a line of showers and thunderstorms that produced small hail in the city of Petoskey. Both broadcast media and the public shared both photo and video evidence of this waterspout via social media.
Cool temperatures aloft over a relatively warm Lake Ontario, combined with a passing trough, brought favorable conditions for waterspouts.
Cool temperatures aloft over a relatively warm Lake Ontario, combined with a passing trough, brought favorable conditions for waterspouts.

A long-duration waterspout was observed via NWS Florida Keys rooftop camera about three to four miles south-southwest of Key West. The waterspout appeared tilted throughout its lifespan, was generally skinny, with the condensation cloud extending about one-fifth the way from cloud base to the horizon.
Public observed a waterspout offshore of Harrington Beach. Location is estimated based off of radar.
Broadcast media relayed a report of a sighting of a waterspout offshore of White Lake over Lake Michigan.
The public reported a sighting of a waterspout just offshore of Holland State Park.
The public reported a waterspout near Holland State Park.
A photo was forwarded from the International Center for Waterspout Research showing a waterspout approximately 15 miles offshore from Indiana Dunes State Park during the afternoon of the 14th.

Broadcast Media (TMJ4) meteorologist pointed out an observe waterspout forming on one of their tower cameras in Racine. Waterspout developed around 1658 UTC with funnel extending from the base of the cloud along with a visible spray ring on the water surface and lasted through at least 1703 UTC. Location is estimated based off of radar.
Multiple Reports of two waterspouts were captured on video east of Mustang Island Park over the open waters. This storm continued SSW towards Malaquite Beach.
A waterspout was observed via a webcam on Pigeon Key, featuring a condensation cloud extending about halfway down from cloud base to the horizon.
A waterspout was sighted just east of Hotel El Conquistador in Fajardo. The waterspout looked very week on the video.
A waterspout was reported by a lifeguard offshore Boynton Inlet.
Broadcast media and public social media posts reported a waterspout spotted in a video just off the coast of Isabela, near Pocita Montones beach.
A waterspout was reported by several members of the public near Annies Place Restaurant and Combate beach, Cabo Rojo. It lasted around 10 minutes and a Spray Ring was visible and recorded.
A trained spotter reported a well-defined waterspout formed off the Long Beach peninsula, and was observed from 1516 to 1523 pm.
Waterspout was reported by a member of the public - a video showing the waterspout was posted on social media as well.
A waterspout was sighted offshore Maunabo. The observer indicated that it quickly dissipated.
Weather spotter reported seeing a waterspout around noon from Fifth Avenue Beach in Manistee, MI.
Weather spotter saw an additional 2-4 waterspouts over the course of fifteen minutes, still at Fifth Avenue Beach in Manistee, MI.
Large waterspout visible from DIP near Cedar Point Pier.
